label chapter_1_part_3_3_cin:
    show cin neutral at center
    with dissolve

    "And Cindy was still up, staring at the campfire while craddling the boy in her arms."

    "She was looking at the boy who was still sleeping."

    cin "This feels nice for some reason..."

    cin "I wonder if he'll stay like that..."

    "And just after she said it, she noticed the boy's head nudging a little."

    "And the boy's eyes slowly fluttered."

    "Seeing this, Cindy's face cheeks blushed red a little bit before she calmed herself down."

    cin "Um... Are you alright, kiddo...?"

    unknown "W-Who... are you...?"

    cin "Shh... D-Don't fret... My name is Cindy. And as you can see... I'm carrying a very big littler of babies in my womb..."

    unknown "W-Why are you craddling me...?"

    cin "Well, me and the others, who are asleep by the way, have decided to pick you up and... yeah... That's how you end up between those... \"melons\"..."

    cin "By the way, do you have a name? Or don't you remember anything...?"

    unknown "Um... It's Kurt..."

    cin "Kurt, huh...? Cute name... Aside from that, do you remember anything...?"

    kurt "Um... Not really..."

    "Hearing this, Cindy began craddling him more."

    cin "I'm sure you need some support... I'm not the one who let people rest on my body, but it looks like you need it..."

    cin "Just rest on my body for now, but don't get any funny ideas, alright...?"

    kurt "A-Alright... But please promise me you won't do anything when I'm sleeping..."

    cin "Sure thing, Kurt... You have my word..."

    hide cin neutral with dissolve

    "And so, both Kurt and Cindy began sleeping"